{"title_page": "Quikjet Airlines", "text_new": "{{Infobox airline\n| airline = Quikjet Cargo\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| logo = File:Quikjet Airlines logo.png\n| logo_size = 150\n| IATA = QO<ref name=\"chavprofile\">{{cite web | url=http://www.ch-aviation.com/portal/airline/QUK | title=Quikjet Airlines | work=[[ch-aviation]] | accessdate=20 February 2017}}</ref>\n| ICAO = FQA<ref name=\"chavprofile\" />\n| callsign = QUIK LIFT<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.faa.gov/documentLibrary/media/Order/7340.2G_Bsc_dtd_1-5-17.pdf | title=JO 7340.2G Contractions | work=[[Federal Aviation Administration]] | date=5 January 2017 | accessdate=20 February 2017 | pages=3\u20131\u201379}}</ref>\n| parent = \n| company_slogan = \n| commenced = 17 February 2016\n| key_people = Nirvan Veerasamy (MD)\n| num_employees = \n| headquarters = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], India\n| aoc = \n| hubs = {{nowrap|[[Indira Gandhi International Airport]] {{small|(Delhi)}}}}\n| focus_cities = \n| frequent_flyer = \n| lounge = \n| alliance = \n| fleet_size = 1\n| destinations = 4\n| website = {{URL|http://www.quikjet.co.in}}\n}}\n\n'''Quikjet Cargo Airlines Pvt. Ltd.''', branded as '''Quikjet Airlines''', is an all-[[cargo airline]] based in [[Bangalore]], India.\n\n==History==\nIt was formed in 2007, promoted by AFL Pvt Ltd. Switzerland-based [[Farnair Switzerland|Farnair]] picked up a 36.2% stake in the airline in February 2012, making AFL the second-largest shareholder with 20.8% stake in the carrier.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/money/report-farnair-to-hike-stake-in-tata-funded-quikjet-1804044|title=Farnair to hike stake in Tata-funded Quikjet}}</ref> QuikJet had operated one of Farnair's twelve ATR 72-200(F)s until March 2013 before temporarily closing shop in anticipation of a B737-400F.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ch-aviation.com/portal/news/19708-farnair-set-to-take-on-four-737-400fs-one-to-go-to-indias-quikjet |title=Farnair set to take on four 737-400Fs; one to go to India's Quikjet |work=[[ch-aviation]]|accessdate= 10 June 2015|date=17 June 2013}}</ref> In May 2015, India's Foreign Investment Promotion Board (FIPB)  approved Farnair's plan to incrementally increase its stake in Quikjet Cargo Airlines from 50.93% to 72.59% involving a minimum total foreign direct investment of Rs. 14.4 Crores. Quickjet plans to launch scheduled domestic cargo services using [[Boeing 737]] aircraft.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://atwonline.com/finance-data/air-contractors-europe-airpost-and-farnair-rebrand-asl-airlines|title=Air Contractors, Europe Airpost and Farnair to rebrand as ASL Airlines |work=[[Air Transport World]]|accessdate= 10 June 2015|date=8 June 2015}}</ref> The airline started scheduled cargo flights on 16 February 2016 using a Boeing 737.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.itln.in/index.php/quikjet-cargos-inaugural-flight-touches-down-at-kiab-bengaluru/|title=QuikJet Cargo's inaugural flight touches down at KIAB, Bengaluru}}</ref>\n\n==Destinations==\nAs of February 2016, Quikjet Cargo flies to the following destinations:\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable toccolours\"\n|-\n! Country (State)\n! City\n! Airport\n! Notes\n! Ref\n|-\n|India ([[Delhi]])||[[Delhi]]||[[Indira Gandhi International Airport]]||{{airline hub}}||align=center|<ref name=\"dest\">{{cite news | url=http://www.ch-aviation.com/portal/news/44096-indias-quikjet-airlines-secures-sovika-logistics-contract | title=India's Quikjet Airlines secures Sovika logistics contract | work=[[ch-aviation]] | date=17 February 2016 | accessdate=7 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|India ([[Karnataka]])||[[Bangalore]]||[[Kempegowda International Airport]]||||align=center|<ref name=\"dest\" />\n|-\n|India ([[Tamil Nadu]])||[[Chennai]]||[[Chennai International Airport]]||||align=center|<ref name=\"dest\" />\n|-\n|India ([[Telangana]])||[[Hyderabad]]||[[Rajiv Gandhi International Airport]]||||align=center|<ref name=\"dest\" />\n|-\n|India  ([[West Bengal]] ||[[Kolkata]] ||[[Netaji Subhash Chandra Bose International Airport]] ||||align=center |<ref name=\"dest\" />\n|-\n|}\n==Fleet==\nAs of April 2019, Quikjet Cargo operates the following aircraft:<ref>{{cite journal|title=Global Airline Guide 2017 (Part One)|journal=Airliner World|issue=October 2017|page=16}}</ref>[[File:Aerospatiale ATR-72-202 QuikJet India HB-AFW, LUX Luxembourg (Findel), Luxembourg PP1367336774.jpg|thumb|Quikjet operated a single [[ATR 72-200F]] from 2011 until 2013.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.airfleets.net/flottecie/QuikJet%20Cargo-history-atr.htm | title=ATR 42/72 in QuikJet Cargo history | work=Airfleets.net | accessdate=7 July 2016}}</ref> The aircraft is shown here at [[Luxembourg Findel Airport]] following its return to [[ASL Airlines Switzerland|Farnair Switzerland]]|207x207px]]\n[[File:Quickjet_737.jpg|alt=|thumb|347x347px|''quickjet 737-400SF taking off from [[Shahjalal International Airport|Dhaka]] Airport.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jetphotos.com/photo/8673889|title=VT-SVA {{!}} Boeing 737-43Q(SF) {{!}} Quickjet India {{!}} Tawkir Hossain|website=JetPhotos|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>|center]]<center>\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jetphotos.com/photo/8673889|title=VT-SVA {{!}} Boeing 737-43Q(SF) {{!}} Quickjet India {{!}} Tawkir Hossain|website=JetPhotos|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Hossain|first=Tawkir|title=English: the quickjet 737 taking off from Dhaka Hazrat Shahjalal Int'l - VGHS|date=2017-08-06|url=https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Quickjet_737.jpg|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0.5em auto\"\n|+Quikjet Cargo fleet\n|- \n! Aircraft\n! In service\n! Orders\n! Notes\n|-\n\n|[[Boeing 737 Classic|Boeing 737-400F]]\n|1\n|\u2013\n|\n|-\n\n!Total\n!1\n!\n!\n|}\nfleet\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<br /></center>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of airlines of India]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons-inline}}\n* {{Official website|http://quikjet.co.in/}}\n\n{{Portalbar|India|Companies|Aviation}}\n{{Airlines of India}}\n\n[[Category:Cargo airlines of India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox airline\n| airline = Quikjet Cargo\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| logo = File:Quikjet Airlines logo.png\n| logo_size = 150\n| IATA = QO<ref name=\"chavprofile\">{{cite web | url=http://www.ch-aviation.com/portal/airline/QUK | title=Quikjet Airlines | work=[[ch-aviation]] | accessdate=20 February 2017}}</ref>\n| ICAO = FQA<ref name=\"chavprofile\" />\n| callsign = QUIK LIFT<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.faa.gov/documentLibrary/media/Order/7340.2G_Bsc_dtd_1-5-17.pdf | title=JO 7340.2G Contractions | work=[[Federal Aviation Administration]] | date=5 January 2017 | accessdate=20 February 2017 | pages=3\u20131\u201379}}</ref>\n| parent = \n| company_slogan = \n| commenced = 17 February 2016\n| key_people = Nirvan Veerasamy (MD)\n| num_employees = \n| headquarters = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], India\n| aoc = \n| hubs = {{nowrap|[[Indira Gandhi International Airport]] {{small|(Delhi)}}}}\n| focus_cities = \n| frequent_flyer = \n| lounge = \n| alliance = \n| fleet_size = 1\n| destinations = 4\n| website = {{URL|http://www.quikjet.co.in}}\n}}\n\n'''Quikjet Cargo Airlines Pvt. Ltd.''', branded as '''Quikjet Airlines''', is an all-[[cargo airline]] based in [[Bangalore]], India.\n\n==History==\nIt was formed in 2007, promoted by AFL Pvt Ltd. Switzerland-based [[Farnair Switzerland|Farnair]] picked up a 36.2% stake in the airline in February 2012, making AFL the second-largest shareholder with 20.8% stake in the carrier.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/money/report-farnair-to-hike-stake-in-tata-funded-quikjet-1804044|title=Farnair to hike stake in Tata-funded Quikjet}}</ref> QuikJet had operated one of Farnair's twelve ATR 72-200(F)s until March 2013 before temporarily closing shop in anticipation of a B737-400F.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ch-aviation.com/portal/news/19708-farnair-set-to-take-on-four-737-400fs-one-to-go-to-indias-quikjet |title=Farnair set to take on four 737-400Fs; one to go to India's Quikjet |work=[[ch-aviation]]|accessdate= 10 June 2015|date=17 June 2013}}</ref> In May 2015, India's Foreign Investment Promotion Board (FIPB)  approved Farnair's plan to incrementally increase its stake in Quikjet Cargo Airlines from 50.93% to 72.59% involving a minimum total foreign direct investment of Rs. 14.4 Crores. Quickjet plans to launch scheduled domestic cargo services using [[Boeing 737]] aircraft.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://atwonline.com/finance-data/air-contractors-europe-airpost-and-farnair-rebrand-asl-airlines|title=Air Contractors, Europe Airpost and Farnair to rebrand as ASL Airlines |work=[[Air Transport World]]|accessdate= 10 June 2015|date=8 June 2015}}</ref> The airline started scheduled cargo flights on 16 February 2016 using a Boeing 737.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.itln.in/index.php/quikjet-cargos-inaugural-flight-touches-down-at-kiab-bengaluru/|title=QuikJet Cargo's inaugural flight touches down at KIAB, Bengaluru}}</ref>\n\n==Destinations==\nAs of February 2016, Quikjet Cargo flies to the following destinations:\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable toccolours\"\n|-\n! Country (State)\n! City\n! Airport\n! Notes\n! Ref\n|-\n|India ([[Delhi]])||[[Delhi]]||[[Indira Gandhi International Airport]]||{{airline hub}}||align=center|<ref name=\"dest\">{{cite news | url=http://www.ch-aviation.com/portal/news/44096-indias-quikjet-airlines-secures-sovika-logistics-contract | title=India's Quikjet Airlines secures Sovika logistics contract | work=[[ch-aviation]] | date=17 February 2016 | accessdate=7 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|India ([[Karnataka]])||[[Bangalore]]||[[Kempegowda International Airport]]||||align=center|<ref name=\"dest\" />\n|-\n|India ([[Tamil Nadu]])||[[Chennai]]||[[Chennai International Airport]]||||align=center|<ref name=\"dest\" />\n|-\n|India ([[Telangana]])||[[Hyderabad]]||[[Rajiv Gandhi International Airport]]||||align=center|<ref name=\"dest\" />\n|-\n|India  ([[West Bengal]] ||[[Kolkata]] ||[[Netaji Subhash Chandra Bose International Airport]] ||||align=center |<ref name=\"dest\" />\n|-\n|}\n==Fleet==\nAs of April 2019, Quikjet Cargo operates the following aircraft:<ref>{{cite journal|title=Global Airline Guide 2017 (Part One)|journal=Airliner World|issue=October 2017|page=16}}</ref>[[File:Aerospatiale ATR-72-202 QuikJet India HB-AFW, LUX Luxembourg (Findel), Luxembourg PP1367336774.jpg|thumb|Quikjet operated a single [[ATR 72-200F]] from 2011 until 2013.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.airfleets.net/flottecie/QuikJet%20Cargo-history-atr.htm | title=ATR 42/72 in QuikJet Cargo history | work=Airfleets.net | accessdate=7 July 2016}}</ref> The aircraft is shown here at [[Luxembourg Findel Airport]] following its return to [[ASL Airlines Switzerland|Farnair Switzerland]]|207x207px]]\n<center>\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jetphotos.com/photo/8673889|title=VT-SVA {{!}} Boeing 737-43Q(SF) {{!}} Quickjet India {{!}} Tawkir Hossain|website=JetPhotos|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Hossain|first=Tawkir|title=English: the quickjet 737 taking off from Dhaka Hazrat Shahjalal Int'l - VGHS|date=2017-08-06|url=https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Quickjet_737.jpg|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0.5em auto\"\n|+Quikjet Cargo fleet\n|- \n! Aircraft\n! In service\n! Orders\n! Notes\n|-\n\n|[[Boeing 737 Classic|Boeing 737-400F]]\n|1\n|\u2013\n|\n|-\n\n!Total\n!1\n!\n!\n|}\nfleet\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n[[File:Quickjet_737.jpg|alt=|thumb|265x265px|quickjet 737-400SF taking off from [[Shahjalal International Airport|Dhaka]] Airport.]]<br /></center>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of airlines of India]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons-inline}}\n* {{Official website|http://quikjet.co.in/}}\n\n{{Portalbar|India|Companies|Aviation}}\n{{Airlines of India}}\n\n[[Category:Cargo airlines of India]]\n", "name_user": "Vppp1", "label": "